# File: knowledge_service/requirements.in
# Service: knowledge-service
# Author: Haffey Enterprises LLC
# Created: 2026-07-21
# Revised: 2026-07-21
# Description: Runtime dependency floors for knowledge-service. Floors follow
#   the house approved-library table (application-code 01-code-structure §1);
#   compiled to a hash-pinned requirements.txt with pip-compile
#   --generate-hashes. Scope is deliberately minimal for the RBT-77 scaffold —
#   nothing speculative is admitted ahead of the story that needs it.
#
#   Deliberate exclusions, each with its authority:
#     - sqlalchemy / asyncpg / alembic — knowledge-service holds no PostgreSQL
#       client by design (SDD-001 §4.1: "No vector, embedding, task-queue,
#       PostgreSQL, or Firestore module exists in this service by design").
#     - httpx / tenacity / circuitbreaker — no outbound service calls exist in
#       this story; they land with the first inter-service call, not before.
#
#   Recorded reach outside the approved-library table: `neo4j`. The graph driver
#   is not in the house table (which binds a PostgreSQL/SQLAlchemy persistence
#   leg); it is mandated here by ADR-002's graph system-of-record decision and
#   SDD-001 §4.2, which makes this service the platform's only driver holder.
#   The floor matches the conformance harness's pinned server line (5.26).

